# Tech Stack Rules
- Framework: React Native with Expo (Expo Router for navigation)
- Language: TypeScript (Strict mode enabled)
- Styling: NativeWind (Tailwind CSS for React Native)
- Backend: Supabase (Auth, Postgres, Storage)
- AI Services: Google Gemini API
- State Management: React Context or Zustand (keep it simple)

# Coding Standards
- Write modular, functional React components.
- Always use TypeScript interfaces/types for props and Supabase database rows.
- Use Expo Router file-based routing standard (app/ directory).
- Style exclusively using NativeWind `className` attributes. Avoid standard React Native `StyleSheet` unless absolutely necessary for complex animations.
- When interacting with Supabase, use the official `@supabase/supabase-js` client.
- Securely store API keys (Gemini, Supabase) using Expo environment variables (`.env`). DO NOT hardcode keys.
- Prioritize mobile-first UI, ensuring safe area views (`SafeAreaView` from `react-native-safe-area-context`) are used to avoid notches.